			<div class="entry">
				<p>Opposing &#8220;free&#8221; and &#8220;open source&#8221; just sounds like a geek troll to me.<br />
Moreover, &#8220;free&#8221; can be restrictive, like in sugar-free or duty-free. It is far from the french word &#8220;libre&#8221; &#8211; which is used internationally and refers to the whole idea of freedom, not just &#8220;free&#8221;.<br />
I think FLOSS is a really good alternative and the proof that all open source, free and libres initiatives just have (barely) the same goals, utilities, users&#8230; Sounds good to me. We have to generalize it.</p>
<p>Open Source Publishing forever. XXX</p>
 
